The paper deals with a packet scheduling problem in computer networks, which involves designing algorithms to transmit packets with different weights and deadlines over a network link. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), algorithms (cs.AL), and game theory (cs.GT). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
